Deidre Rubenstein https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deidre_Rubenstein 0 Deidre Rubenstein (born 1948) is an Australian television and theatre actress,as well as a dramatist and playwright well known for her performance in Australian soap operas and main stage dramatic roles. She has won the Australian Film Institute (AFI) Award as Best Actress. Rubenstein graduated from the National Institute of Dramatic Art in 1967 and has worked extensively in live theatre, television, films and as a narrator of audio books. She has produced a significant body of work as a narrator of audio books and has won several awards in this field.
